        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 1:19PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 118 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles southeast of Uptown Charlotte, or near East Charlotte, moving
northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Matthews, Reedy Creek Park, Mint Hill, South Charlotte, Southpark
Mall, East Charlotte, Stallings, and Central Charlotte.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
